01:18:17,901 --> 01:18:21,234
I hear you've
taken several road losses.

796
01:18:21,304 --> 01:18:24,899
I'm left in dire shape,
if the truth be known.

797
01:18:26,276 --> 01:18:29,211
A calamity
can come on any man.

798
01:18:32,949 --> 01:18:35,281
An odd spirit takes over.

799
01:18:36,453 --> 01:18:40,082
You can touch a person
with your bare hand...

800
01:18:40,156 --> 01:18:42,283
and his spirit
can come into you.

801
01:18:42,359 --> 01:18:45,954
I've heard that said.

802
01:18:46,029 --> 01:18:48,998
Olaf Singletary came
to see me earlier this morning...

803
01:18:49,065 --> 01:18:51,693
determined to find
this girl of his.

804
01:18:51,768 --> 01:18:55,636
But I suppose he hasn't come yet.
I've not seen him here.

805
01:18:55,705 --> 01:18:59,573
And she's not here.
No.

806
01:18:59,643 --> 01:19:02,111
Well, there.

807
01:19:02,178 --> 01:19:04,578
Just as I told him.

808
01:19:15,191 --> 01:19:18,957
And you don't know where she is,
do you, August?

809
01:19:19,029 --> 01:19:20,963
I don't know.

810
01:19:23,033 --> 01:19:26,002
There, you see.

811
01:19:27,237 --> 01:19:30,764
And you've not seen her
anywhere along the way?

812
01:19:30,840 --> 01:19:34,367
Yes, I have seen her.

813
01:19:34,444 --> 01:19:38,175
You saw her, but you didn't help her.
It's against the law to help her.

814
01:19:38,248 --> 01:19:40,182
I know it is.

815
01:19:50,293 --> 01:19:52,818
I suppose you think...

816
01:19:52,896 --> 01:19:56,593
I'm not involved.

817
01:19:56,666 --> 01:19:58,600
But I am...

818
01:19:59,669 --> 01:20:03,070
because people--
even this morning--

819
01:20:03,139 --> 01:20:05,573
have come through my gate...

820
01:20:05,642 --> 01:20:08,668
and said laws have been broken...

821
01:20:08,745 --> 01:20:12,442
property rights violated.

822
01:20:15,318 --> 01:20:18,253
A spell came over me,
Mr. Wright.

823
01:20:19,823 --> 01:20:23,759
I did a hundred things strange,
nothin' customary.

824
01:20:26,062 --> 01:20:27,996
You explain it to me.

825
01:20:29,733 --> 01:20:32,065
 

826
01:20:33,937 --> 01:20:37,805
 
Well, what say we prepare a defense?

827
01:20:37,874 --> 01:20:39,865
Is there to be a trial?

828
01:20:39,943 --> 01:20:43,242
Of a type.

829
01:20:44,280 --> 01:20:46,271
I suppose many a person...

830
01:20:46,349 --> 01:20:50,410
might steal a good cow,
and once word went out...

831
01:20:50,487 --> 01:20:52,887
the thief might
have slaughtered it.

832
01:20:54,257 --> 01:20:59,160
As for the boar, you were
caught in the river's current.

833
01:20:59,229 --> 01:21:02,130
And then this girl
ran out of the bushes...

834
01:21:02,198 --> 01:21:04,462
and you did what
any decent body would do.

835
01:21:04,534 --> 01:21:08,095
You agreed to take her
to Olaf Singletary.

836
01:21:08,171 --> 01:21:10,605
The geese?

837
01:21:12,242 --> 01:21:14,176
Forget the geese.

838
01:21:16,112 --> 01:21:19,081
They flew away up on the ridge.

839
01:21:19,149 --> 01:21:21,709
I saw them myself, flying away.

840
01:21:25,054 --> 01:21:28,080
No one will burn this man's
house because of geese.

841
01:21:30,894 --> 01:21:33,727
Burn my house?

842
01:21:37,867 --> 01:21:40,768
 
  You men stay here.

843
01:21:57,253 --> 01:21:59,448
This is no place for women.

844
01:21:59,522 --> 01:22:02,719
She's known her own mind
since a girl.

845
01:22:07,030 --> 01:22:08,964
 

846
01:22:14,170 --> 01:22:16,104
You have her?

847
01:22:16,172 --> 01:22:18,800
He saw her for a few minutes
last night...

848
01:22:18,875 --> 01:22:22,242
and then she ran off
on the way to your house.

849
01:22:22,312 --> 01:22:24,507
I won't accept that.

850
01:22:24,581 --> 01:22:26,515
I will accept her.
That's all!

851
01:22:26,583 --> 01:22:30,075
She's not here, Olaf,
as I told you.

852
01:22:32,789 --> 01:22:34,723
Where is she?

853
01:22:34,791 --> 01:22:37,555
Now, there's no need for this.

854
01:22:37,627 --> 01:22:40,790
We have talked to this poor man
a long while...

855
01:22:40,864 --> 01:22:43,856
and I assure you,
she is not here.

856
01:22:43,933 --> 01:22:45,867
And as you told me...

857
01:22:45,935 --> 01:22:48,961
you yourself examined his cart,
and so did I.

858
01:22:56,412 --> 01:22:58,346
Please.

859
01:22:58,414 --> 01:23:00,348
Where is Anna?

860
01:23:03,286 --> 01:23:06,380
He can't tell you that.

861
01:23:12,562 --> 01:23:14,826
 

862
01:23:19,202 --> 01:23:21,966
Wh-- Where did you see her?

863
01:23:23,940 --> 01:23:25,874
At a creek.

864
01:23:28,478 --> 01:23:31,970
I first saw her
three mornings ago near the gap.

865
01:23:34,384 --> 01:23:37,012
Then she came to my camp...

866
01:23:37,086 --> 01:23:39,554
and I felt sorry for her.

867
01:23:44,127 --> 01:23:47,290
Since my wife died,
I've been lost...

868
01:23:47,363 --> 01:23:50,298
and I was needin' help
as much as anybody.

869
01:23:53,169 --> 01:23:55,603
I gave her some bread, milk...

870
01:23:57,240 --> 01:24:00,175
and I brought her
along the road.

871
01:24:06,916 --> 01:24:09,783
He can't be trusted
to tell the truth.

872
01:24:09,852 --> 01:24:13,117
He's not accountable, Olaf.

873
01:24:14,357 --> 01:24:16,257
 
No!

874
01:24:16,326 --> 01:24:20,319
It's all right.
It's all right.

875
01:24:35,645 --> 01:24:38,079
I'll not deny what I did.

876
01:24:40,717 --> 01:24:43,652
I don't want to be...

877
01:24:43,720 --> 01:24:46,120
only what I was.

878
01:25:03,272 --> 01:25:05,206
 

879
01:25:13,216 --> 01:25:15,150
 

880
01:25:16,352 --> 01:25:20,584
I'll burn him out.
It's the law.

881
01:25:20,657 --> 01:25:23,353
Well, burn him out,
if it pleases you.

882
01:25:23,426 --> 01:25:27,624
It seems not to matter to him,
so why ought it matter to me?

883
01:25:27,697 --> 01:25:29,824
I wash my hands of him.

884
01:25:29,899 --> 01:25:33,130
He's got the prophet's look
about him.

885
01:25:34,871 --> 01:25:38,136
He cares not a whit
for property.

886
01:26:10,573 --> 01:26:13,508
He never mentioned the barn,
August.

887
01:26:19,449 --> 01:26:23,385
If you want any dresses, Mina,
you better go get 'em.

888
01:26:28,991 --> 01:26:31,926
We can at least try
and stop them, August.

889
01:26:31,994 --> 01:26:35,760
Olaf made his deal:
House for the girl.

890
01:27:35,024 --> 01:27:37,254
I was right well-to-do.

891
01:27:38,394 --> 01:27:41,830
All in a day or two,
I've lost everything.

892
01:27:45,034 --> 01:27:48,299
But I've never been so proud.

